38:25.520 --> 38:27.305
James, grab the chair.

38:27.348 --> 38:30.046
What do you mean, get the chair?
We're not doing this, Vanessa.

38:30.960 --> 38:32.266
VANESSA:
Sit.

38:32.310 --> 38:34.007
There's tape in the top drawer.

38:34.050 --> 38:35.574
Tape?
I don't think you understand.

38:35.617 --> 38:37.053
This is happening.

38:37.097 --> 38:39.795
-Tape, Vanessa?
-Yes.

38:39.839 --> 38:42.929
Just tape him up
while we figure out what to do.

38:43.756 --> 38:46.715
He's a cop.
Who knows what he'll pull?

38:46.759 --> 38:48.238
We -- We need a minute, okay?

38:48.282 --> 38:50.110
So just tape him up for now

38:50.153 --> 38:52.765
so we can figure it out
without him able to do anything.

38:54.375 --> 38:56.769
He's a cop.

38:56.812 --> 38:58.292
Please.

38:58.336 --> 39:00.990
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

39:03.253 --> 39:05.038
Please.

39:05.081 --> 39:07.388
Please, honey.

39:08.737 --> 39:12.132
[ Music continues ]

39:12.175 --> 39:13.916
Put your arms down.

39:14.569 --> 39:17.833
Put your arms down.
Put -- Put them on the sides.

39:17.877 --> 39:19.052
[ Music ends ]

39:19.095 --> 39:20.575
Thank you.

39:20.619 --> 39:22.969
[ Tape stretching ]

39:26.364 --> 39:28.975
Fuck.
Fuck, man.

39:43.293 --> 39:45.426
This is by far
the dumbest fucking thing

39:45.470 --> 39:47.167
you could possibly be doing
right now.

39:47.210 --> 39:49.387
-You realize that, right?
-Shut up.

39:49.430 --> 39:51.127
Let me talk to her, okay?

39:51.171 --> 39:53.303
I'm gonna figure this out.
This is very out of character.

39:53.347 --> 39:55.305
More tape, baby.

39:55.349 --> 39:56.524
Clearly.

39:56.568 --> 39:58.265
[ Dramatic music plays ]

40:00.572 --> 40:01.834
[ Whispering ]
Come here.

40:03.749 --> 40:05.228
[ Whispering ]
Come here!

40:08.406 --> 40:10.364
Have you gone completely insane?

40:10.408 --> 40:12.105
I just want to talk to the man.

40:12.148 --> 40:14.324
-He brought this on himself.
-Did he?

40:14.368 --> 40:15.717
I want him to answer
my questions.

40:15.761 --> 40:18.111
-Why? Why?
-Exactly. Why?

40:18.154 --> 40:20.983
You have any idea how much
fucking trouble you're in?

40:21.027 --> 40:22.637
-Can we talk?
-We're talking.

40:22.681 --> 40:24.596
-VANESSA: We're talking.
-JAMES: We'll be right back.

40:24.639 --> 40:26.380
-Why are you being polite?
-Hey!

40:30.906 --> 40:33.648
[ Music builds, ends ]

40:37.826 --> 40:39.132
Okay.

40:47.923 --> 40:50.578
This is too much, Vanessa.

40:50.622 --> 40:51.927
Too much this time.

40:51.971 --> 40:54.016
-Not far enough, if you ask me.
-Oh?

40:55.191 --> 40:56.715
So, what's next on your agenda?

40:56.758 --> 40:59.413
Should I go and waterboard him,
babe?

40:59.457 --> 41:01.371
James.

41:03.852 --> 41:08.335
This is a man who has exhibited
no regard for common decency

41:08.378 --> 41:09.902
or human life.

41:09.945 --> 41:13.079
This is a man who yelled
a racial slur at your wife.

41:13.122 --> 41:16.735
And this is an officer
who gets off killing Black kids.

41:16.778 --> 41:18.171
There are people who are hired

41:18.214 --> 41:20.173
to take care of people like him,
okay?

41:20.216 --> 41:22.392
We -- We are not those people.

41:22.436 --> 41:26.005
Do you trust those people
or do you trust me?

41:26.048 --> 41:27.397
Us.

41:31.271 --> 41:33.578
What's your plan?
Hmm?

41:33.621 --> 41:36.406
We are going to have
a civilized conversation --

41:36.450 --> 41:38.496
I just used
fucking shipping tape

41:38.539 --> 41:40.715
to duct-tape the man
to the back of a fucking chair,

41:40.759 --> 41:42.543
and you're talking about
civilized?!

41:42.587 --> 41:43.936
Civilized?!
Oh, my God!

41:43.979 --> 41:46.460
Oh, my fucking God.

41:46.504 --> 41:48.331
Fucking shipping tape.

41:56.775 --> 41:58.733
Fine.

41:58.777 --> 42:01.867
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

42:10.745 --> 42:13.574
JAMES: What do --
What do you mean, "fine"?

42:15.620 --> 42:17.143
Just fine.

42:18.361 --> 42:20.538
Do as you see fit,

42:20.581 --> 42:23.628
man of the house...
king of it all.

42:23.671 --> 42:25.978
I'll follow you, oh,
he who stands when urinating.

42:26.021 --> 42:28.197
That is bullshit,
and you -- you -- you know it.

42:28.241 --> 42:32.027
I think that you are missing
the magnitude of this,

42:32.071 --> 42:33.812
the potential.

42:34.769 --> 42:38.730
Black people, brown people,
LGBTQ people,

42:38.773 --> 42:40.340
poor people, immigrants --

42:40.383 --> 42:42.168
He was probably taught to fear
all of them!

42:42.211 --> 42:44.039
Your kidnapping him at gunpoint,

42:44.083 --> 42:46.215
I'm sure that quelled
all of his fears, okay?

42:46.259 --> 42:48.261
Mission accomplished.

42:48.304 --> 42:50.437
No, James.

42:50.480 --> 42:52.787
No.
We have a captive listener.

42:53.353 --> 42:56.661
We are capable of having
a rational conversation

42:56.704 --> 42:59.011
with a man who is stuck.

42:59.054 --> 43:01.622
He is stuck in a generational
cycle of hate.

43:01.666 --> 43:04.146
-No.
-Yes.

43:04.190 --> 43:05.887
[ Sighs ]
No.

43:05.931 --> 43:07.628
Yes.

43:10.805 --> 43:12.764
[ Music ends ]

43:12.807 --> 43:14.853
This right here.

43:14.896 --> 43:16.855
This is what you do.

43:17.943 --> 43:19.727
You create a necessity for chaos

43:19.771 --> 43:21.860
so that your projections
can thrive.

43:21.903 --> 43:22.948
Yep.

43:27.692 --> 43:29.650
I've been seeing a therapist.

43:29.694 --> 43:32.305
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

43:32.348 --> 43:33.872
-What?
-I've noticed some of your --

43:33.915 --> 43:36.222
our-- our patterns.

43:36.265 --> 43:38.528
You get all worked up,
and then you get me there, too.

43:38.572 --> 43:41.009
And then my feelings
and my frustrations,

43:41.053 --> 43:43.272
they have to be yours
or they're -- they're not valid.

43:43.795 --> 43:45.144
What therapist?
When?

43:45.187 --> 43:46.972
You escalate everything
until we're stuck

43:47.015 --> 43:48.843
in this counterproductive cycle,

43:48.887 --> 43:53.500
until all that's left is my
anxiety and my bitterness, babe.

43:53.543 --> 43:55.676
And Sheila thinks that's part
of our co-dependency.

43:55.720 --> 43:57.678
-Sheila?
-And honestly, I'm starting --

43:57.722 --> 43:59.027
Of course it's a Sheila.

43:59.071 --> 44:00.942
-Don't say it like that.
-Like what?

44:00.986 --> 44:04.163
Like you're having a secret
rendezvous with Sheila?

44:04.206 --> 44:05.599
That is not fair, Vanessa, okay?

44:05.643 --> 44:08.167
Do not talk to me about fair.

44:08.210 --> 44:09.690
[ Music continues ]

44:09.734 --> 44:11.866
JAMES: Listen. I started
doing this because of you.

44:11.910 --> 44:14.303
-VANESSA: You made that clear.
-JAMES: No, not -- Not b--

44:14.347 --> 44:16.175
Not because of you, babe.

44:16.218 --> 44:17.698
Foryou so that I could be
a better man.

44:17.742 --> 44:19.613
Thank you so much.

44:19.657 --> 44:22.616
I feel great that my husband is
seeing a woman behind my back.

44:22.660 --> 44:24.923
How can you talk to him
rationally about all this

44:24.966 --> 44:27.186
but you can't even talk
to your own husband

44:27.229 --> 44:28.709
about his fucking mental health

44:28.753 --> 44:31.712
without accusing me of fucking
my therapist?

44:35.847 --> 44:38.197
Does Sheila know
you're keeping therapy a secret?

44:38.240 --> 44:40.765
What does Sheila think
about that?

44:41.766 --> 44:42.854
[ Music continues ]

44:42.897 --> 44:44.377
JAMES:
Okay. Okay.

44:44.420 --> 44:46.292
Okay.
Listen. Um...

44:46.945 --> 44:51.123
We're not foreign adversaries,
babe.

44:51.166 --> 44:54.866
All right?
We -- We are domestic allies.

44:55.605 --> 44:57.651
Let's not forget that.

44:58.434 --> 45:00.001
Did you get that from therapy?

45:00.045 --> 45:02.482
-That is not from therapy!
-Then where is it from?

45:02.525 --> 45:04.745
It is not from therapy.
It is from Sheila.

45:04.789 --> 45:06.573
And Sheila happens to be
a therapist.

45:06.616 --> 45:08.662
I don't want to talk to Sheila!

45:08.706 --> 45:10.490
[ Door rattling,
metal squeaking ]

45:10.533 --> 45:12.710
-Fuck!
-James!

45:12.753 --> 45:14.712
James!

45:16.539 --> 45:17.584
[ Metal clanks ]

45:17.627 --> 45:18.933
VANESSA:
Stop.

45:19.542 --> 45:21.719
[ Dramatic music plays ]

45:23.111 --> 45:24.460
Get up.

45:25.287 --> 45:27.420
[ Music continues ]

45:53.794 --> 45:56.405
[ Music builds, continues ]

46:29.003 --> 46:30.744
[ Music slows, ends ]

46:35.880 --> 46:37.316
This is fucking ridiculous.

46:37.359 --> 46:38.708
VANESSA:
You're right. It is.

46:38.752 --> 46:40.232
It should never have to come
to this.

46:40.275 --> 46:42.756
James, can we please
just continue our sidebar

46:42.800 --> 46:44.410
so we can have
the necessary conversation

46:44.453 --> 46:46.238
with Officer Brian afterwards?

46:46.281 --> 46:48.936
[ Doorbell rings ]

46:52.984 --> 46:54.289
Jamal.

46:54.333 --> 46:56.030
-Shit.
-Fuck.

46:56.074 --> 46:57.597
Help! Help!
I'm being held against my will!

46:57.640 --> 46:59.642
Cover his mouth. Tape his mouth.

47:00.730 --> 47:02.036
JAMES:
My God.

47:02.080 --> 47:03.864
-Let's just not answer.
-He has a key.

47:03.908 --> 47:05.474
You gave him a key?

47:05.518 --> 47:07.781
-For emergencies, Vanessa.
-What kind of emergency?

47:07.825 --> 47:10.001
In case we run out
of rolling papers?

47:10.044 --> 47:12.830
[ Cellphone buzzing, ringing ]

47:16.616 --> 47:19.532
[ Ringing stops ]

47:22.013 --> 47:24.406
Is this what you were
reaching for?

47:24.885 --> 47:26.974
[ Doorbell ringing ]

47:28.846 --> 47:31.022
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

47:31.631 --> 47:33.546
[ Whispering ]
Hurry up. Hurry up.

47:33.589 --> 47:35.243
Okay. Okay.
Okay.

47:35.287 --> 47:36.549
Vanessa, put the gun away.

47:36.592 --> 47:38.594
Oh. Okay.
Okay.

47:39.944 --> 47:42.076
Okay.
Open the door.

47:42.120 --> 47:44.339
[ Music builds, continues ]

47:47.038 --> 47:48.213
JAMES:
Brother!

47:48.256 --> 47:49.910
-What's happening?
-What's up?

47:49.954 --> 47:51.346
Hi, guys!

47:51.390 --> 47:52.565
Brother.

47:52.608 --> 47:53.871
JAMAL:
What's up?

47:53.914 --> 47:55.568
[ Insects chirping ]

47:55.611 --> 47:57.439
Hey.

48:00.094 --> 48:01.487
Oh, come on in.

48:01.530 --> 48:03.315
CANDY:
Okay.

48:03.358 --> 48:05.143
JAMES: How you doing?
What's going on?

48:05.186 --> 48:07.319
There it goes.
What's up, man?

48:07.362 --> 48:09.887
-You want to...
-Oh. Sorry. Yeah.

48:11.323 --> 48:13.891
[ Dramatic music plays ]

48:14.326 --> 48:16.241
JAMAL:
Wow.

48:17.285 --> 48:19.244
Oh, snap.

48:22.551 --> 48:25.554
Since when do y'all play piano?
[ Chuckles ]

48:26.599 --> 48:28.949
I'm sorry.
I have to use the bathroom.

48:28.993 --> 48:31.256
Onyx has me going nonstop.

48:31.299 --> 48:33.432
-Onyx?
-JAMAL: We landed on the name.

48:33.475 --> 48:37.305
Yeah. Onyx is one of the most
powerful healing stones.

48:37.349 --> 48:40.526
It balances chakras.
It promotes energy flow.

48:40.569 --> 48:42.876
It's a grounding gem.
Harmonious.

48:42.920 --> 48:45.313
Yeah. It's black
like the motherland, baby.

48:45.357 --> 48:47.315
My king.
I see you.

48:47.359 --> 48:49.317
-The bathroom's just up-
-CANDY: To the right, right?

48:49.361 --> 48:51.015
Okay.
Thank you.

48:51.058 --> 48:53.104
JAMAL: Man, I haven't been here
since y'all remodeled.

48:53.147 --> 48:55.541
-Shit look fly, though.
-JAMES: Thank you.

48:55.584 --> 48:57.325
Vanessa, she handled most of it.

48:57.369 --> 48:59.762
Just, uh, blew out the wall
and added a bathroom.

48:59.806 --> 49:01.764
JAMAL:
All kind of shit.

49:01.808 --> 49:04.506
Got new floor and everything.
Can I get the rest of the tour?

49:04.550 --> 49:06.073
-You told me about this office.
-No.

49:06.117 --> 49:08.032
The office actually
isn't finished yet, right?

49:08.075 --> 49:09.337
Bedroom's the same.

49:09.381 --> 49:11.905
We broke the bank
on the living room.

49:11.949 --> 49:14.386
Tell me about it, right?
And the kitchen, of course.

49:14.429 --> 49:17.041
-We should go right in there.
-This shit was expensive.

49:17.084 --> 49:19.217
VANESSA:
I'll make a drink and...

49:24.004 --> 49:26.006
Are we too early?

49:26.572 --> 49:28.835
It looks like dinner's
still in the grocery bags.

49:28.878 --> 49:30.271
Uh, yeah.

49:30.315 --> 49:32.317
We are, um,
running a little behind.

49:32.360 --> 49:34.188
I -- Work went late,

49:34.232 --> 49:38.149
and there was this guy with a
clipboard at the grocery store,

49:38.192 --> 49:40.890
and then I had to get --
get gas.

49:40.934 --> 49:42.805
I thought those things
was electric.

49:42.849 --> 49:45.721
Right. I had to go to the
gas station with the car wash

49:45.765 --> 49:47.071
to get my car washed.

49:47.114 --> 49:50.552
In the meantime,
there is alcohol.

49:52.511 --> 49:54.469
[ Dishes clanking ]

49:54.513 --> 49:56.558
[ Door closes ]

49:59.213 --> 50:00.475
JAMAL:
You know, it's funny.

50:00.519 --> 50:02.042
I read this article
the other day.

50:02.086 --> 50:04.262
-You read an article.
-Yeah. I read all the time, bro.

50:04.305 --> 50:06.003
Okay?
That's all I do.

50:06.046 --> 50:08.396
That's why I have one of these
location devices on me,

50:08.440 --> 50:11.225
'cause you can get information
in a snap of your fingers.

50:11.269 --> 50:13.358
As I was saying, I read
this article the other day.

50:13.401 --> 50:15.055
Couples who maintain
different opinions

50:15.099 --> 50:16.709
on things of little consequence

50:16.752 --> 50:18.363
are more likely
to stay together.

50:18.406 --> 50:20.582
That's the title I read.
I didn't read the whole thing.

50:20.626 --> 50:22.062
But you know what I mean, right?

50:22.106 --> 50:24.717
Babe, you didn't tell them.

50:26.197 --> 50:27.589
Tell us what?

50:27.633 --> 50:29.069
-JAMAL: Sorry, babe.
-CANDY: It's okay.

50:29.113 --> 50:30.462
I'm vegan.

50:30.505 --> 50:31.941
I thought they knew, sweetie.
I'm sorry.

50:31.985 --> 50:34.422
It's okay.
I'm carcass-free since 2010.

50:34.466 --> 50:36.076
Yeah.

50:36.120 --> 50:39.297
Well, I'm sure James knew
and just forgot to tell me.

50:39.340 --> 50:42.648
It isfree-range and organic.

50:42.691 --> 50:46.739
Well, not really free if you're
born to be slaughtered, right?

50:47.261 --> 50:50.090
Free range just means they're
being let out their cages.

50:50.134 --> 50:51.700
But being in a cage?

50:51.744 --> 50:53.920
That's a mind-set.

50:53.963 --> 50:55.617
You know what I'm saying?

50:56.792 --> 50:59.012
Hardly ever, Jamal.
Hardly ever.

50:59.056 --> 51:00.274
Oh, I'm interested.

51:00.318 --> 51:01.884
You really want to
get him started

51:01.928 --> 51:03.886
on his back-to-Africa
conspiracy shit right now?

51:03.930 --> 51:05.540
Candy, what can I get you
to drink?

51:05.584 --> 51:07.455
Uh, water, please.

51:07.499 --> 51:08.848
We have juice.

51:08.891 --> 51:11.851
It's vegan. [ Chuckles ]
Certified organic.

51:11.894 --> 51:13.635
Oh, they just give
that sticker out

51:13.679 --> 51:15.985
to anybody
who's the highest bidder.

51:16.029 --> 51:17.596
Water will be fine.
Thank you.

51:17.639 --> 51:19.728
James, you would be the one
to dismiss my thoughts

51:19.772 --> 51:21.339
as a conspiracy, right?

51:21.382 --> 51:22.905
Easiest way
to invalidate somebody

51:22.949 --> 51:24.733
and discredit them
is calling them crazy.

51:24.777 --> 51:27.084
Makes you look good at your job
but limits your skull, bro.

51:27.127 --> 51:29.347
We understand that you're
a successful Black man and all,

51:29.390 --> 51:32.654
but you're just living
under the white man's thumb.

51:33.829 --> 51:35.179
Not always.

51:35.222 --> 51:37.398
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

51:37.442 --> 51:40.619
[ Spices rattling ]

51:50.150 --> 51:52.631
-VANESSA: There you go.
-Thank you.

51:58.463 --> 52:00.247
[ Music continues ]

52:00.291 --> 52:01.727
[ Exhales deeply ]

52:03.816 --> 52:05.426
I'm sorry.

52:05.470 --> 52:08.125
I...I didn't know you were on
the whole vegan trend.

52:08.168 --> 52:09.387
I do have pasta.

52:09.430 --> 52:11.606
Gluten-free, too, actually,
so --

52:11.650 --> 52:12.955
But this is great.

52:12.999 --> 52:14.435
-Thank you.
-JAMAL: It's good.

52:16.045 --> 52:17.743
Oh, Vanessa,
I got you something.

52:17.786 --> 52:19.092
Hold on.

52:19.136 --> 52:20.789
Mm...

52:26.404 --> 52:28.145
-Here.
-Vanessa.

52:28.188 --> 52:29.624
Oh.

52:34.455 --> 52:36.153
It's sage.

52:36.892 --> 52:37.980
For me?

52:38.024 --> 52:39.721
CANDY:
You burn it.

52:39.765 --> 52:41.767
You know, to cleanse the energy
of the house.

52:41.810 --> 52:43.769
Out with the bad juju,
in with the...

52:43.812 --> 52:45.205
Setting off the smoke alarms.

52:45.249 --> 52:46.467
[ Laughter ]

52:46.511 --> 52:47.947
Smoke alarms.

52:48.426 --> 52:51.516
I'm sorry. I just thought
it could help with your flow.

52:52.430 --> 52:53.518
-That's all.
-Oh.

52:53.561 --> 52:55.694
Myflow.
Right.

52:56.260 --> 52:58.523
I'm so sensitive to energy
right now.

52:58.566 --> 53:01.308
I guess 'cause of the pregnancy,
it just heightens.

53:01.352 --> 53:03.223
That's very thoughtful of you.
Yeah.

53:03.267 --> 53:05.660
How's work at the shop, Candy?

53:05.704 --> 53:07.749
CANDY: Wellness center.
It's going good. Yeah.

53:07.793 --> 53:10.143
It's nice to work in a place

53:10.187 --> 53:12.841
that fosters such a sense
of peace

53:12.885 --> 53:15.235
while I'm pregnant, you know?

53:15.279 --> 53:16.845
JAMAL: Pay ain't good,
but, you know,

53:16.889 --> 53:18.456
come home with a lot of rocks.

53:18.499 --> 53:19.805
-CANDY: Crystals.
-Crystals, baby.

53:19.848 --> 53:21.546
I'm sorry.
Crystals.

53:21.589 --> 53:23.243
CANDY:
And my work isn't about money.

53:23.287 --> 53:25.071
-It's about fulfillment.
-JAMAL: Yeah.

53:25.114 --> 53:27.029
But you do have
health insurance.

53:27.073 --> 53:29.423
-CANDY: Of course.
-JAMAL: We got health insurance.

53:29.467 --> 53:31.773
For the most part,
we plan to bring our baby

53:31.817 --> 53:33.645
into this world
the homeopathic way.

53:33.688 --> 53:37.214
You know, hospitals are so,
so bad for women of color.

53:37.257 --> 53:39.085
-Oh.
-CANDY: It's weird.

53:39.128 --> 53:42.828
It's bad vibes, bringing a life
into a place where people die.

53:43.307 --> 53:44.395
-Right.
-That's crazy.

53:44.438 --> 53:48.181
So, how are you going to...

53:48.225 --> 53:49.443
Natural birth.

53:49.487 --> 53:51.315
So -- So no hospitals,
no vaccines.

